in.teramatrix.googleservices

Class GoogleServices

  • java.lang.Object
    • in.teramatrix.googleservices.GoogleServices

  • public class GoogleServices
extends java.lang.Object
    Main Class of the module that will be capable to call all the services from one place. Even Those services can be also called individually, but this class will provide more encapsulated methods. Each method of this class contains its documentation comments please refer them to know more. Although GoogleAnalyst, Locator, FusedLocationProvider like services are not used in this class, you have to use them directly without an instance of this class.
    Author:
    Mohsin Khan
    Date:
    3/18/2016

      • getPlaces

        public java.util.ArrayList<Place> getPlaces(java.lang.String key,
                                            com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng location,
                                            java.lang.String... places)
                                     throws java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException,
                                            java.lang.InterruptedException
        To call Google's Places API synchronously, this method method is designed. Method will show how to use PlacesExplorer
        Parameters:
        key - Your application's API key. This key identifies your application for purposes of quota management and so that places added from your application are made immediately available to your app.
        location - The latitude/longitude around which to retrieve place information. This must be specified as latitude,longitude.
        places - Restricts the results to places matching at least one of the specified types. like "hotel", "bar", "restaurant"
        Returns:
        an ArrayList of type Place
        Throws:
        java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • getDistances

        public java.util.ArrayList<Distance> getDistances(java.lang.String origin,
                                                  java.lang.String... destinations)
                                           throws java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException,
                                                  java.lang.InterruptedException
        A method to describe the use of DistanceCalculator class. It will synchronously call the Distance Matrix API and bind results to ArrayList of Distance.
        Parameters:
        origin - One or more locations to use as the starting point for calculating travel distance and time. But this class only supports a single origin right now. It's further implementations may expand the origins.
        destinations - One or more locations to use as the finishing point for calculating travel distance and time.
        Returns:
        ArrayList of Distance
        Throws:
        java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException
        java.lang.InterruptedException
        See Also:
        Distance

      • executeDistanceCalculator

        public void executeDistanceCalculator(java.lang.String key,
                                      java.lang.String origin,
                                      DistanceCalculator.DistanceListener listener,
                                      java.lang.String... destinations)
        This method will call Google's Direction Matrix API and results will be thrown to the listener after JSON parsing.
        Parameters:
        key - APIs in each platform require a specific type of key. The Google Maps Distance Matrix API will only work with a Server key. APIs of the same platform can use the same key. It is for free users.
        origin - One or more locations to use as the starting point for calculating travel distance and time. But this class only supports a single origin right now. It's further implementations may expand the origins.
        listener - an implemented version of DistanceCalculator.DistanceListener
        destinations - One or more locations to use as the finishing point for calculating travel distance and time.
